FuncDef:
The nat alarm user-table disable command disables the trap or log alarm function for user tables.
The undo nat alarm user-table disable command enables the trap or log alarm function for user tables.
By default, the trap and log alarm function for user tables are enabled.
CLIs: undo nat alarm user-table log disable
undo nat alarm user-table trap disable

ParaDef.Info:
Disables or enables the trap function for user tables.
-

Enables or disables the log function for the number of user tables.
-

ExtraInfo:
Usage Scenario
To disable the trap or log alarm function for user tables, run the nat alarm user-table disable command.
You can use the nat alarm user-table { log | trap } disable command to enable or disable the function of sending and logging the user table threshold alarm, but cannot control the user table exhaustion alarm and log function.
Precautions
In VS mode, this command is supported only by the admin VS.
